[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    378[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m1[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mCross-clinician context swap on a shared rolling cart.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Clinician A re-fetches EHR state showing Mr. Smith's chart open. Clinician A says "show last labs." Between the re-fetch and the execute, Clinician B taps in at the cart and switches the EHR to Mrs. Davis's chart. The execute then proceeds against the EHR's API with the resolved patient ID (Mr. Smith's, from the re-fetch), but the EHR's display now shows Mrs. Davis's chart; the labs render in a confusing way (the voice system shows Mr. Smith's labs in the voice client overlay; the EHR shows Mrs. Davis's chart). Or worse, the execute calls the EHR API in a way that depends on the EHR's session context (e.g., "set the active chart section to allergies for the currently-active patient") and the action operates on Mrs. Davis's chart against Clinician A's intent.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    379[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    380[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m2[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mSingle-clinician multi-window context drift.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Clinician A has two browser tabs open, both with SMART on FHIR launches. The voice command's session_context references one tab; the clinician's keyboard-and-mouse interaction switched the other tab to a different patient. The re-fetch returns the state from one tab; the execute operates against the other.[K
