[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    396[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m1[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mRead commands are HIPAA-grade access events.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m A duplicate [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mopen_patient[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m command produces two chart-open events in the EHR's audit log. The patient's access-record now shows the chart was opened twice when the clinician intended to open it once. This is a HIPAA-disclosure-record fidelity concern: the access-record should reflect the clinician's actual access events, not the voice system's retry behavior.[K
