[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    531[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    532[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m SMART on FHIR access tokens have a configurable but typically short lifetime (5-60 minutes for most EHR vendors). The recipe handles staleness at session-open (Step 1A) by rejecting and prompting re-launch, but does not specify what happens when the token expires mid-session. A clinician's voice-navigation session may last for hours of patient encounters; the token will expire mid-session for any non-trivial deployment. The architecture should specify:[K
